e a superconducting spherical shell with a\ntime-varying surface charge; (ii) a two-level atom experiment in which the\natomic spectrum acquires FM sidebands when it is placed inside a spherical\nshell whose exterior mass is sinusoidally varying with time. The former leads\nto a time-varying internal magnetic field, and the latter leads to a\ntime-varying gravitational redshift.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Nov 2014 17:38:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-14"}
